From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Amaan Qureshi <git@amaanq.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 6/14] octeon: enable PKO3 LMTST in CvmMemCtl

Mainline never sets CvmMemCtl[LMTENA]/[LMTLINE] since no in-tree driver used
LMTST, so PKO3 TX faults (AdES) on the LMTDMA doorbell. Set them in
octeon_user_io_init per CPU.

Signed-off-by: Amaan Qureshi <git@amaanq.com>
---
 arch/mips/cavium-octeon/setup.c |     6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/setup.c b/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/setup.c
--- a/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/setup.c
+++ b/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/setup.c
@@ -617,8 +617,14 @@
 	/* R/W If set, CVMSEG is available for loads/stores in user
 	 * mode. */
 	cvmmemctl.s.cvmsegenau = 0;
 
+	/* LMTDMA faults with AdES unless LMTENA is set and LMTLINE = 2. */
+	if (octeon_has_feature(OCTEON_FEATURE_PKO3)) {
+		cvmmemctl.s.lmtena = 1;
+		cvmmemctl.s.lmtline = 2;
+	}
+
 	write_c0_cvmmemctl(cvmmemctl.u64);
 
 	/* Setup of CVMSEG is done in kernel-entry-init.h */
 	if (smp_processor_id() == 0)
-- 
2.54.0
